
# Using the Decima Framework

A primary use of the Decima Framework is as an API. To use Decima as an API, he following dependency can be added to your POM to use this library.

```xml
<dependency>
  <groupId>${project.groupId}</groupId>
  <artifactId>decima-xml-assessment</artifactId>
  <version>${project.version}</version>
</dependency>

```

This will automatically include the [decima-core] and [decima-xml] dependencies.

The following source packages are included in this release:

- [gov.nist.secauto.cpe.common](apidocs/gov/nist/secauto/cpe/common/package-summary.html): contains functions common to both the naming and matching packages

   This package contains the following class:

   - [gov.nist.secauto.cpe.common.WellFormedName](apidocs/gov/nist/secauto/cpe/common/WellFormedName.html): provides methods to construct an unbound CPE name

- [gov.nist.secauto.cpe.naming](apidocs/gov/nist/secauto/cpe/naming/package-summary.html): contains classes related to the CPE naming algorithms

   This package contains the following classes:

   - [gov.nist.secauto.cpe.naming.CPENameBinder](apidocs/gov/nist/secauto/cpe/naming/CPENameBinder.html): provides methods to bind a WellFormedName to the CPE URI and formatted string forms
   - [gov.nist.secauto.cpe.naming.CPENameUnbinder](apidocs/gov/nist/secauto/cpe/naming/CPENameUnbinder.html): provides methods to unbind a CPE URI or formatted string into a WellFormedName

- [gov.nist.secauto.cpe.matching](apidocs/gov/nist/secauto/cpe/matching/package-summary.html): contains classes related to the CPE matching algorithm

   This package contains the following class:

   - [gov.nist.secauto.cpe.matching.CPENameMatcher](apidocs/gov/nist/secauto/cpe/matching/CPENameMatcher.html): provides methods to test a match between two different CPE names

